<H1>Concepts&nbsp;Review</H1>
<p><font size="5"><i><b>COM+</b></i> is the cornerstone of a frame work of 
technologies designed to support the development of large-scale distributed 
applications on the Windows platform.</font></p>
<p><font size="5" color=red>Two basic concepts:</font></p>
<p><font size="5">(1) Context: is an object within an operating system process 
that provides a specific set of run-time service</font></p>
<p><font size="5">(2) Causality:&nbsp; is a distributed chain of COM+ method 
call that spans any number of contexts in any number of processes, possibly 
involving multiple machines. </font></p>
